okens either in cookies (default) or sessions. The _get_secret() method (lines 221-251) handles both cases.\n\nDecorators in django/views/decorators/csrf.py:\n- csrf_protect (line 7): Applies CsrfViewMiddleware protection to individual views\n- csrf_exempt (lines 50-68): Marks views as exempt from CSRF protection\n- requires_csrf_token (lines 22-28): Ensures token availability without rejecting invalid tokens\n- ensure_csrf_cookie (lines 42-47): Forces CSRF cookie generation\n\nTemplate integration:\n- The csrf context processor in django/template/context_processors.py (lines 18-34) provides the token to templates\n- The CsrfTokenNode in django/template/defaulttags.py (lines 73-95) renders the hidden form input containing the token\n- The csrf_input helper in django/template/backends/utils.py (lines 7-11) provides the form input HTML\n\nThe csrf_failure view in django/views/csrf.py (lines 22-80) handles rejected requests and displays appropriate error messages."
